The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Chinsurah, April 3: Police tonight stopped a rally for Trinamuls Serampore candidate Kalyan Banerjee midway when a skit called Buddha noy, shanti chai (Want peace, not Buddha  which rhymes with the Bengali word for war, juddha) was being staged. Cops said no permission had been sought for it. A mob had earlier protested the sale of CDs purportedly showing CPM atrocities in Singur and Nandigram at the venue.        
	Calcutta: A motor- cyclist was beheaded late on Friday night when the two-wheeler collided with a truck at the Sinthi crossing on BT Road. Police identified the victim as Balai Dewan, 40. He was hit by the truck, coming from the opposite direction, while trying to take a right turn. The head landed several yards away from the body.        
	Santiniketan: Visva-Bharati VC Rajat Kanta Ray carried a bucket of water to a hostel at midnight on Thursday to calm students demonstrating outside his residence after three days without water in toilets.                                                                                                                                                                        
